From: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com [mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com] On Behalf Of
Misty Dawn
Sent: Monday, May 11, 2009 1:37 AM
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] The Seven - interesting tidbit of info









Gets weirder. Even stranger none of the police scanner codes I can find
online so far seem to follow along with thier callout codes for seven. Not
sure if its something new they implemented or what I will ask when I get a
chance. The trooper I was talking to has been on the force quite a few years
but I know they have been implementing some changes on how they do things
just not sure if thats one of them.



Misty

--- On Mon, 5/11/09, Misty Dawn &lt;bulletbabea@...&gt; wrote:


From: Misty Dawn &lt;bulletbabea@...&gt;
Subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] The Seven - interesting tidbit of info
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Date: Monday, May 11, 2009, 2:28 AM


Yeah I hadnt heard of it until today. I just looked at him and said glad hes
alive and thanks for the info I find the 7 thing interesting.



Ive had spirits say they were seven before when I asked what it was they
always lead me to the conclusion it was a label for the group speaking this
info just made me go hmmm then wow once it sunk in. Interesting
synchronicity anyway.



Misty

--- On Mon, 5/11/09, Zack Widup &lt;w9sz.zack@gmail. com&gt; wrote:


From: Zack Widup &lt;w9sz.zack@gmail. com&gt;
Subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] The Seven - interesting tidbit of info
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups .com
Date: Monday, May 11, 2009, 2:04 AM

I guess police still use those codes. Emergency agencies such as ESDA now
follow the FEMA Incident Command System/National Incident Management System
which requires all communications to be in plain English (no codes).

Zack




On Sun, May 10, 2009 at 11:31 PM, Misty Dawn &lt;bulletbabea@ yahoo.com
&lt;http://us.mc329.mail.yahoo.com/mc/compose?to=bulletbabea@...&gt; &gt;
wrote:




Tonight at work I was talking to a state trooper, there had been an
accident. I asked him if there were any deaths (it was very very bad) and he
said he didnt know so he got on his radio and called in and asked them if it
was a 7 at the site. They told him negative, and he told me the little boy
who was the worst off was still alive. I asked him why did you ask them if
it was a 7. He said code 7, I was asking them if they were dead. So if you
ever hear anyone call 7 over the radio that means someones dead.



Just thought I would pass that on. I find it interesting since I know alot
of us have heard this before when used to describe who is speaking rather
than a name they say seven.



Misty












